  "instructions": [
    {
      "step": 1,
      "text": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>to prep, so get your baking trays and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p>",
      "imageUrl": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-1762184966169-x200.jpg"
    },
    {
      "step": 2,
      "text": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Separate your <strong>duck leg[s]</strong> from the <strong>white duck fat </strong>and <strong>duck jelly </strong>(you'll use these in different parts of the recipe!)</p>",
      "imageUrl": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1698925998946-x200.jpg"
    },
    {
      "step": 3,
      "text": "<p>Add the<strong> duck leg[s]</strong>, <strong>Chantenay carrots </strong>and <strong>waxy</strong> <strong>potatoes</strong> to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!)</p><p>Top the potatoes and carrots with the <strong>duck fat </strong>and season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 30-35 min or until the duck leg[s] is golden and crispy and the potatoes are tender</p>",
      "imageUrl": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-3-1706694043900-x200.jpg"
    },
    {
      "step": 4,
      "text": "<p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
      "imageUrl": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1698926012362-x200.jpg"
    },
    {
      "step": 5,
      "text": "<p>When the duck has about 5 min cooking time left, boil a kettle</p><p>Add the <strong>duck jelly</strong> to a measuring jug<strong> </strong>with your<strong> chicken stock mix </strong>and<strong> cornflour</strong></p><p>Mix until fully combined, then stir in 150ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [195ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [275ml]</span><strong> boiled water</strong>, a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and set aside – this is your <strong>gravy mix</strong></p>",
      "imageUrl": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1698926015864-x200.jpg"
    },
    {
      "step": 6,
      "text": "<p>Once the potatoes are tender and the duck is golden, remove the tray[s] from the oven and spread your<strong> spiced plum chutney </strong>over the duck</p><p>Return to the oven for a final 2-3 min or until caramelised – this is your <strong>plum glazed roast duck</strong></p><p>Meanwhile, put the <strong>gravy mix</strong> in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 2 min or until thickened, stirring halfway – this is your<strong> gravy</strong></p>",
      "imageUrl": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-2-1706694090702-x200.jpg"
    },
    {
      "step": 7,
      "text": "<p>Add your<strong> blanched peas </strong>to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over them to refresh them</p><p>Crush the <strong>potatoes</strong> firmly with a spatula or the bottom of a mug</p><p>Add a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up – these are your <strong>crushed potatoes</strong></p>",
      "imageUrl": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-3-1706694097202-x200.jpg"
    },
    {
      "step": 8,
      "text": "<p>Serve the <strong>plum glazed roast</strong> <strong>duck </strong>with the <strong>crushed potatoes</strong>,<strong> roast carrots </strong>and <strong>peas </strong>to the side</p><p>Pour over the<strong> gravy</strong> and season with a generous pinch of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Dig in!</p>"
    }
  ],
